cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper deals with computer vision and robotics, specifically the problem of estimating dense optical flow from sparse lidar data for autonomous vehicles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with robotics and autonomous vehicles, which could place it in cs.RO (Robotics and Control). The paper also involves the use of deep learning, which could place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
